error mail directory is not writable error when running alpine stanford answers stanford university stanford answers error mail directory is not writable error when running alpine categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home error mail directory is not writable error when running alpine search this site the mail directory is not writable error most often occurs when a user is over quota or not enough free space is available to accommodate all messages waiting to be downloaded from the mail server adequate space must be freed or mail downloaded to a temporary location instead of a user's home directory to fix the error download mail to a temporary location use alpine to open the temporary mail folder for inspection alpine f tmp sunetid mail mail downloaded to tmp in this way will be deleted after approximately 24 hours if no further action is taken any messages that should be kept indefinitely should be saved to a permanent folder in alpine or the tmp sunetid mail file should be copied or moved to mail after sufficient space is made available by default alpine is configured to use imap for mail transfer instead of pop which allows permanent storage of messages on the mail server itself if you changed alpine to use pop consider restoring the imap configuration if you need help submit a helpsu request unix email stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
